re #23280

* have below task provider
* run either of the tasks
* :bug: the command runs but the arguments aren't passed along

```ts
        provideTasks(token) {

            const tasks: vscode.Task[] = [];
            tasks.push(new vscode.ShellTask('ls -la', 'ls', { args: ['-la'] }))
            tasks.push(new vscode.ShellTask('node', 'node', { args: ['-e', '"console.log(Date.now())"'] }))
            return { tasks };
        }
```

Testing #23311 

1. Register a sample SCM Provider extension with following contributions in package.json

```json
"contributes": {
		"commands": [
			{
				"category": "Sample SCM Provider",
				"command": "sample.scm.init",
				"title": "Initialize sample SCM",
				"icon": {
					"dark": "resources/add.svg",
					"light": "resources/add.svg"
				}
			}
		],
		"menus": {
			"scm/title": [
				{
					"command": "sample.scm.init"
				}
			]
		}
	}
```

Since `SCMProvider.contextKey` is optional, IMO above contribution is correct. 

With this, above command `Initialize sample SCM` appears in all SCM Providers. 

IMO SCM Core should have the ability to control to show only commands from the current active provider.
